[[File:Atheros_Intellon_1200_AFE.jpeg|thumb|Atheros Intellon 1200 AFE-Chip as companion for an INT 5500 PowerLine-IC]] An '''analog front-end''' ('''AFE''' or '''analog front-end controller AFEC''') is a set of analog signal conditioning circuitry that uses sensitive analog amplifiers, often operational amplifiers, filters, and sometimes [[application-specific integrated circuit]]s for sensors, radio receivers, and other circuits to provide a configurable and flexible electronics functional block, needed to interface a variety of sensors to an, antenna, [[analog to digital converter]] or in some cases to a [[microcontroller]].
AFE hardware modules are used as interface sensors for many kinds of analog and digital systems, providing hardware modularity. For example, [[Texas Instruments]] markets health monitoring AFEs as the ADS1298, AFE4400 and AFE4490.<ref>{{Cite news |url= http://www.eetimes.com/document.asp?doc_id=1262310 |title=Inside TI's ADS1298 analog front end for health monitoring |work= EE Times |author= Treena Grevatt |date= August 9, 2012 |accessdate= October 3, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title= AFE4400: Integrated Analog Front End for Heart Rate Monitors and Low Cost Pulse Oximeters |url= http://www.ti.com/product/afe4400 |work= Product web page |publisher= Texas Instruments |accessdate= October 3, 2013 }}</ref> A [[radio frequency]] AFE is used in radio receivers, known as an [[RF front end]].<ref>{{Cite news |url= http://www.eetimes.com/document.asp?doc_id=1276331 |title= What's in an RF Front End? |work= EE Times |author= Christopher Bowick |date= February 4, 2008 |accessdate= October 3, 2013 }}</ref> [[Atmel]] markets analog front-ends for [[smart meter]]s.<ref>{{Cite web |title= Atmel Acquires IDT’s Smart Metering Product Line |url= http://www.atmel.com/microsite/smart-energy-solutions/default.aspx |work= Product web page |publisher= Atmel |accessdate= October 3, 2013 }}</ref> [[Analog Devices]] markets a CN0209 product for test and measurement applications.<ref>{{Cite web |title= CN0209: Fully Programmable Universal Analog Front End for Process Control Applications |url= http://www.analog.com/en/circuits-from-the-lab/CN0209/vc.html |work= Product web page |publisher= Analog Devices |accessdate= October 3, 2013 }}</ref>
